definitions.definition: The act or process in which an agent (person or computer) parses something (a text, a program).
examples: Parsing an Old English text can be difficult.

definitions.definition: An instance of that act or process; a parse .
examples: A parsing of a sentence about a horse can yield several possible results.

definitions.definition: Any result of such an instance; a parse ; an acceptation .
examples: Upon review, for the word horse , the parsing "animal" was rejected in favor of the parsing "piece of gymnastic equipment".

main_definition: ( uncountable ) The act or process in which an agent (person or computer) parses something (a text, a program).
secondary_definitions: ( countable ) An instance of that act or process; a parse .
( countable ) Any result of such an instance; a parse ; an acceptation .
